No, it can not be wraped up that simply.  Sure, it would be easy to say the first time I smoked pot it was becasue someone else talked me into it.  Easy, but hardly true.  The truth is that I was curious about the drug and I wanted to know what it was like.  Was this becasue my mother didn't convince me that it was bad for me and illegal, of COURSE not.  I knew this already, and reagardless of what she told me, I still would have tried it.<br>
I realize I am comparing apples to Fords here, but my point is that parents can ONLY do so much.  As Maus stated, you can move hevan and Earth trying to get through, and sometimes they will STILL not listen to you.  If you are going to sit there and testify that this makes you a bad parent, so be it.  I simply don't agree.  For the record, I used smoking pot becasue it is probably the mildest example I can come up with.  Trust me, there are PLEANTY more, but I'm not about to turn this into some twisted confessional.  <br>
My mother knows what I have done in my younger days, since I tell her about it when I visit her.  We laugh about it over coffee sometimes.  She is relieved I lived through some of it, but I would not say for an SECOND she was a bad parent.  If you think you will keep your kid under lock and key, monitor her friends, control her interaction with all outside of her immediate family, and hold her to a RIGID curfew, fine.  Good luck, and I will tell you now that some of the WORST examples of drunks and fuck-ups I saw as a young 20-something had childhoods JUST like that.  They are going to do things you don't agree with.  I decide my feelings for you as a role-model on what you do AFTER they have done that.<br>
Hardly gospel, but it is MY feelings. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=316564" target="top">Tib</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
