<br>
My computer is the only one my girls have access to that has internet access. I allow them to surf the web. And as tacky as it sounds, I sit RIGHT beside them while they surf the net. Yeah, it's an invasion of their privacy. Do I care? Hell NO! I do it cuz I love my children. Plain and simple. I want to know what they're doing, who they're talking to, who they're hanging with, where they're at, when they'll be home, and if they're not home, why the hell not?!  I'm strict. I know it. My girls know it. And my girls know why. They don't always like it, but they sure do respect it. <br>
<br>
Any parent out there who doesn't take an active interest in what their children are doing needs to be bitchslapped....  <p>&quot;Rational thinking is overrated&quot;<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
